-lrb- cnn -rrb- president abraham lincoln never lost his ardor for the united states to remain united during the civil war .
in his second inaugural address he attempted to salve the nation with an eloquent summation of his philosophy and plans for putting it into practice .
the spirit of lincoln 's second inaugural was self-evident on april 9 , 1865 -- 150 years ago -- when confederate gen. robert e. lee dramatically surrendered his approximately 28,000 troops to union general ulysses s. grant at appomattox courthouse -lrb- mclean house -rrb- in virginia .
over 600,000 americans -- northerners and southerners alike -- had perished in the bloody civil war .